dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Visegrad, sheet Y-26. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dc_description_s: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Visegrad. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. Danube zone grid. Gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1949. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With a Serb and Croat glossary. Intelligence reports up to Jan. 1943. Compiled and drawn by the War Office, 1944. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete. Geographic designation is given as Yugoslavia it is Serbia and Montenegro; and Bosnia ans Herzegovina.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1949.
